# ipradasgomez.github.io — workflow

Personal site at https://tekkisma.es. Vue 3 + Vue Router + Tailwind + Vite, deployed via GitHub Actions.

## Branches

- `develop` — default working branch. All site changes happen here.
- `main` — production releases only. Never commit site work directly to `main`.

Do not push or run deploy unless the user asks.

## Local dev (Docker)

```bash
make dev           # Docker dev server at http://127.0.0.1:5173
make dev-down      # stop dev server
make build-check   # local build (same as CI)
make release       # local build + PR develop→main + wait for CI checks
make deploy        # alias for release
make setup-hooks   # install pre-commit validations (once)
```

**Build Check** runs on every PR to `develop` and `main`. Branch protection on both branches should require the `build` status check.

Do not push directly to `main`. Never merge PRs until Build Check passes.

## Routing

- Use **Vue Router** (`src/router/index.js`).
- Add pages as views in `src/views/`.
- Use `<RouterLink>` for internal navigation, not `<a href>` for app routes.
- Build generates `404.html` from `index.html` for GitHub Pages SPA support.

## Static data ("fake API")

- JSON files live in `public/data/` (e.g. `site.json`, `projects.json`).
- Fetch at runtime via `src/api/fetchJson.js` — files are copied to `dist/data/`, not bundled.
- Prefer this over hardcoding large datasets in components.

## Site structure

```
src/
  router/index.js
  views/
  api/fetchJson.js
  App.vue
  main.js
public/
  data/           # static JSON data
  favicon.svg
docker-compose.yml
makefiles/          # dev.mk, github-deploy.mk, hooks.mk
.githooks/
.github/workflows/build-check.yml
.github/workflows/deploy.yml
```

## AI behavior

- Work on `develop` unless the user explicitly targets another branch.
- Prefer minimal, focused diffs; match existing Vue/Tailwind patterns.
- Do not create git commits or push unless the user requests it.
- For production release, suggest `make release` (or `make deploy`).
